The paper is about semantic text search and information retrieval, which are core topics in computer science. The use of spreading activation algorithm and ontology also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of ontology and semantic search also suggests a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The experiments on a benchmark dataset suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and evaluation of information retrieval systems (cs.SI).
